  "notes": "Standard Thai. Abugida with 44 consonant letters in three tone classes (low/mid/high) that interact with 4 tone marks to produce 5 tones: mid, low, falling, high, rising. Inherent vowel is /o/ (short). Vowels written around consonants (above, below, before, after). This spec covers consonant letters and common vowel diacritics; full tone calculation requires syllable analysis.",
